CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 21, 1941, pg. 2, reads: "Pittsburgh Visitor - Mrs. Addie E. Gattewood, well known citizens of Durham, N. C., who recently spent and enjoyable vacation with her sister-in-law, Mrs. Cora Hill of 547 Francis Street, Pittsburgh. Mrs. Gattewood visited relatives in Pittsburgh whom she had not seen in 21 years. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Addie E. Gattewood wearing dark jacket, light colored blouse with ruched placket and circular lace trim, and pearl necklace and earrings, posed in Harris Studio
